  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"ddb\">\n<p>You transform up to ten centipedes, three spiders, five wasps, or one scorpion within range into &amp;Reference[giant]{giant} versions of their natural forms for the duration. A centipede becomes a &amp;Reference[giant]{giant} centipede, a spider becomes a &amp;Reference[giant]{giant} spider, a wasp becomes a &amp;Reference[giant]{giant} wasp, and a scorpion becomes a &amp;Reference[giant]{giant} scorpion.</p>\n<p>Each creature obeys your &amp;Reference[vocal]{verbal} commands, and in combat, they act on your turn each round. The GM has the statistics for these creatures and resolves their actions and movement.</p>\n<p>A creature remains in its &amp;Reference[giant]{giant} size for the duration, until it drops to 0 hit points, or until you use an action to dismiss the effect on it.</p>\n<p>The GM might allow you to choose different targets. For example, if you transform a bee, its &amp;Reference[giant]{giant} version might have the same statistics as a &amp;Reference[giant]{giant} wasp.</p>\n</div>",
